definition.value: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group.
A 4-carbon, branched hydroxy fatty acid and intermediate in the metabolism of valine.

An oligopeptide that is N-[(1E,3S)-6-amino-1-(methanesulfonyl)-6-oxohex-1-en-3-yl]-N(2)-carboxy-L-leucinamide in which the carboxy group is protected by a Cbz group. It is a SARS-CoV-2 Nsp5 main protease inhibitor that inhibits SARS-CoV-2 replication.

An oligopeptide that is N-[(1E,3S)-6-amino-1-(methanesulfonyl)-6-oxohex-1-en-3-yl]-N(2)-carboxy-L-leucinamide in which the carboxy group is protected by a (3-ethynylphenyl)methyl group. It is a SARS-CoV-2 Nsp5 main protease inhibitor that inhibits SARS-CoV-2 replication.

A member of the class of triazolopyridines that is [1,2,4]triazolo[1,5-a]pyridin-5(1H)-one substituted by phenyl, ethylsulfanediyl, cyano, amino and cyano groups at positions 1, 2, 6, 7 and 8, respectively.
The R-enantiomer of eliprodil.
The S-enantiomer of eliprodil.
A 3-hydroxymethylcephalosporin having a (5-amino-5-carboxypentanoyl)amino group at the 7-position.
A cyclic dicarboxylic anhydride that is 1,3,3a,4,7,7a-hexahydro-2-benzofuran carrying oxo groups at positions 1 and 3.
A member of the class of piperidines that is piperidine substituted by a 2-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-hydroxyethyl group at position 1 and by a 4-fluorobenzyl group at position 4.

A member of the class of benzazepines that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1H-2-benzazepine substituted by a (2S)-2-{[(2E)-2-(hydroxyimino)acetyl]amino}propyl group at position 2. It is an antidote currently in development for nerve agent poisoning.

A nucleoside analogue that is N(4)-hydroxycytidine in which the 5'-hydroxy group is replaced by a (2-methylpropanoyl)oxy group. It is the prodrug of the active antiviral ribonucleoside analog N(4)-hydroxycytidine (EIDD-1931), has activity against a number of RNA viruses including SARS-CoV-2, MERS-CoV, and seasonal and pandemic influenza viruses. It is currently in phase III trials for the treatment of patients with COVID-19.
A nucleoside analogue that is cytidine which carries a hydroxy group at the N(4)-positon. It has broad-spectrum antiviral activity against influenza, SARS-CoV , SARS-CoV-2 and MERS-CoV.
An aminobenzoate that is the conjugate base of 3-amino-2,4-dihydroxybenzoic acid arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

Actinomycin X2, is a chemotherapy medication used to treat a number of types of cancer and has strong antimicrobial activity against Gram-positive bacteria, including MRSA and non-MRSA. It is given by injection into a vein. Most people develop side effects. Common side effects include bone marrow suppression, vomiting, mouth ulcers, hair loss, liver problems, infections, and muscle pains. Other serious side effects include future cancers, allergic reactions, and tissue death at the site of injection. Use in pregnancy may harm the baby. It is in the cytotoxic antibiotic family of medications. It is believed to work on DNA and  Isoleucyl-tRNA synthetase (IleRS).
A UDP-sugar having D-glucose as the sugar component.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 3,3-dimethylbutyric acid substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
A member of the class of aminoxyls that is TEMPO carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 4. It is a radical scavenger which exhibits anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties.
A member of the class of aminoxyls that is TEMPO carrying an oxo group at position 4.
An aliphatic nitrile that is 2-methylpropane substituted by a cyano group at position 1.
A primary nitroalkane that is 2-methylbutane substituted by a nitro group at position 4. It is a herbivore-induced plant volatile found in the leaves of Oenothera biennis.
A member of the class of phylloquinones that consists of 1,4-naphthoquinone having methyl and phytyl groups at positions 2 and 3 respectively. The parent of the class of phylloquinones.
A member of the class of aminoxyls that is TEMPO carrying a methoxy substituent at position 4.
A member of the class of aminoxyls that is TEMPO carrying a carboxy group at position 4.
A member of the class of aminoxyls that is TEMPO carrying an amino group at position 4.
A piperidinecarboxamide that is TEMPO carrying an acetamido group at position 4.
A piperidinecarboxamide that is TEMPO carrying an 2-iodoacetamido group at position 4.
A member of the class of piperidines that is TEMPO carrying a maleimido group at position 4.
A member of the class of piperidines that is TEMPO carrying a benzoyloxy group at position 4.
A member of the class of piperidines that is TEMPO carrying a methacryloyloxy group at position 4.
